## DISPOSITION — TRIAGED-TO-BACKLOG [2026-06-21 02:05 ET, conductor]

**Verdict: legitimate but LOW-leverage; moved to Active backlog Tier 3, inbox closed.** Unlike the two FOMC-eve items, this is NOT entry-hunting — it's a *defensive do-no-harm gate* (suspend bear entries 30 min after a ★★★-level false-break-and-recover at the open) protecting the LIVE BEARISH_REJECTION edge, framed in the OP-16 anchor framework. So it is NOT superseded by the entry-hunting STOP. BUT it is single-day evidence (one −$204 trade) and C28/L156/L139/L141 establish that exit/gate refinements on bearish_rejection are diminishing-returns (locally optimal). Not worth a chef fire against the current "exploit vwap, not refine bear-rejection" pivot. Preserved verbatim as queue item **FALSE-BREAK-OPEN-CARRY-GATE (Tier 3)** so it survives; inbox item closed to stop per-fire phantom re-reads. Promote to a chef fire only if (a) ≥3 more days exhibit the same false-break-open → bear-trap pattern, or (b) J prioritizes bear-rejection exit hardening.
